The paper discusses a machine learning problem of multi-dimensional classification, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a Monte Carlo approach for efficient classifier chains, which is a method used in machine learning for multi-label classification, a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the theoretical and empirical study of payoff functions, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper compares its proposed method with other related methods, which is a common practice in computational linguistics (cs.CL). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, which is the sub-category for machine learning.
